    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON E1200I I-BEAM - INSPECTION - TIE ROD</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>TIE ROD</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The threaded portion of each tie rod end must be inserted completely in the cross tube split
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200706">Figure 6</hotlnk>). This is essential for adequate clamping. Replace
                components if this fit cannot be obtained.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200706" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200706" filename="../figg02/G0200706.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Cross Tube Split</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Ball and socket torque (exclusive of boot resistance) should be 5 in-lbs. (0.6 N&#183;m) or
                more on disconnected tie rod end assemblies. Replace assemblies that test less than 5 in-lbs. (0.6 N&#183;m).
                Loose assemblies will adversely affect steering performance and may prevent adjustment of the steering
                assembly to alignment specifications.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
